    {
      "id": "beo_vs_zno_ged",
      "type": "ged",
      "description": "BeO vs ZnO: both wurtzite (P6_3mc), structurally identical. The crystal_graph_v4 builder reports CN=13 for BeO and CN=14 for ZnO due to the adaptive cutoff giving slightly different second/third-shell counts in the two cells. With polyhedral / angle features the cost would be exactly zero; under the current bond-only representation the residual CN-mismatch produces a small non-zero cost.",
