    {
      "id": "nacl_vs_zno_ged",
      "type": "ged",
      "description": "NaCl (rock-salt, octahedral CN=6 nominally) vs ZnO (wurtzite, tetrahedral CN=4 nominally): the textbook structural distinction is sharp, but the crystal_graph_v4 builder uses an adaptive cutoff that includes second/third coordination shells for wurtzite (CN=14) while keeping rock-salt at first-shell-only (CN=6). The graph-level representations therefore differ in bond-count density \u2014 but the sibling-bond filter masks much of that gap during matching. Without polyhedral / angular connectivity in the graph, the distinguishing features of these two families are not fully expressible. Cost is left bounded only from above; future polyhedral-aware graphs should recover a meaningful lower bound here.",
      "graph_a": "NaCl_mp-22862",
      "graph_b": "ZnO_mp-2133",
      "cif_a": "NaCl_mp-22862.cif",
      "cif_b": "ZnO_mp-2133.cif",
