      "description": "ZnO (wurtzite, hexagonal) vs ZnS (zinc blende, cubic): both have identical local bond environments at the graph level \u2014 same Zn cation, tetrahedrally-derived high-CN bonding profile, single anion class. The wurtzite/zinc-blende distinction is a stacking polytype difference (ABAB vs ABCABC) that lives in dihedral angles and longer-range topology \u2014 features the current crystal_graph_v4 builder does not capture (no polyhedral connectivity, no torsion encoding). Under the current graph implementation these are equivalent, so cost must be near zero. Distinguishing polytypes would require adding polyhedral connectivity / angular features to the graph.",
