    {
      "id": "baco3_vs_ba3pbo_ged",
      "type": "ged",
      "description": "BaCO3 (witherite, Pmcn \u2014 molecular CO3 carbonate with planar CO3 triangles and Ba 9-coordinate to O) vs Ba3PbO (cubic antiperovskite Pm-3m \u2014 3D cation framework with O at body-center, Pb at corner).  Both share an ABX3-type 5-atom unit cell with one 12-coord cation (Ba) and one 3-coord cation (C in BaCO3 / role-swapped O in Ba3PbO), but the underlying topology is incompatible: BaCO3 has isolated CO3 anion molecules, Ba3PbO has a corner-sharing octahedral X-site framework.  Currently a known false positive \u2014 the algorithm reaches cost=0 via role-swap + cross-CN fallback + NN-list rectification.  This test pins the philosophical answer; the cost lower bound is what we'd want once second-shell or stricter rectification rules are in place.",
      "graph_a": "BaCO3_mp-4559",
      "graph_b": "Ba3PbO_mp-29242",
      "cif_a": "BaCO3_mp-4559.cif",
      "cif_b": "Ba3PbO_mp-29242.cif",
