    {
      "id": "baco3_vs_srtio3_ged",
      "type": "ged",
      "description": "BaCO3 (witherite carbonate) vs SrTiO3 (cubic Pm-3m perovskite): no shared cation, different stoichiometric layout, fundamentally different topology (planar CO3 anionic groups vs corner-sharing TiO6 octahedral framework).  Cleanest of the BaCO3 false-positive trio because there's no shared element to anchor a misleading mapping; if the algorithm still scores this near zero, the failure is clearly in the bond-multiset/role-swap/NN-rectification stack rather than in element identity.",
