    {
      "id": "ccl3f_vs_cclf3_ged",
      "type": "ged",
      "description": "CCl3F (CFCl3, R-11) vs CClF3 (CF3Cl, R-13): under the bond-graph encoding (element identity not used in edge cost) the two are graph-isomorphic \u2014 central sp3 carbon bonded to 4 CN=1 anions, with CCl3F's 8-FU cell as a 4\u00d7 supercell of CClF3's 2-FU cell.  Cost=0 is correct, and every atom should be mapped (the k-loop must pick k=4 with MULTIPLY, not k=1 with sibling vacancies).",
