    {
      "id": "mnco3_polymorphs_ged",
      "type": "ged",
      "description": "MnCO3 mp-18814 (calcite, R-3c, 10 atoms / 2 FU, Mn CN=6, all O CN=3) vs MnCO3 mp-1078473 (different polymorph, 20 atoms / 4 FU, Mn CN=9, mixed O CN=3,4,5).  Different topologies (calcite vs aragonite-like high-coordination polymorph), so cost should be non-zero \u2014 but every atom must be mapped: the imbalanced MULTIPLY-mode assignment currently leaves two A-side O atoms as sibling vacancies (ids [5, 9]) while other A-Os get over-mapped to 3 B-slots, which is a bug in MULTIPLY-mode bookkeeping.",
      "graph_a": "MnCO3_mp-18814",
      "graph_b": "MnCO3_mp-1078473",
      "cif_a": "MnCO3_mp-18814.cif",
      "cif_b": "MnCO3_mp-1078473.cif",
      "assertions": [
