      "description": "SrTiO3 vs ReO3: ReO3 is an empty perovskite \u2014 Sr is assigned a free vacancy, Ti maps to Re (both CN=6 B-site), O maps to O (CN=6 vs CN=2 cross-CN fallback). With the Sr vacancy correctly zeroing out O's Sr-bonds, the O and Ti environments match exactly and cost should be near zero.",
